Ex- BBN housemate Tbaj has revealed what gesture she finds rude in men According to the reality star, it is ungentlemanly for a man to pass through a door without first allowing a lady to pass through. She said that she finds the gesture rude and then questions the upbringing of men who do that. She said: “I find it rude when a man walks through the door before a lady. Who raised you?”   Nigeria in dire need of overhauling – Comedian AY     Ex-BBN Tacha, Mercy Ike reconcile     Mayorkun blames FG for Kaduna train attack   However, fans and followers reacted to this statement with some agreeing, others against it and others making light of it. @9yommie tweeted: “What is wrong with it? Aren’t we equal anymore?” @ally-citizen said: “Actually, it’s wrong. Etiquettes demand the gents opens for the lady to walk pass but omo”. @Egi_nupe wrote: “Who raised a disabled adult that can’t open door for herself?”